# Data Dictionary — obadage2024 (Citation Contexts for AI Reproducibility)
Source: github.com/lamps-lab/ccair-ai-reproducibility (Zenodo 10.5281/zenodo.10895748).
Files:
- citation_context_label_summary.json: per cited-paper (RS_xxx) counts of citation
  contexts in each sentiment class (-2, -1, 0, 0.5, 1). 1=positive, -1/-2=negative.
- citation_counts_for_cited_papers.json: per cited-paper {manual_count_after_2021,
  manual_count_all_retrieved, citationCount}.
- MLRC_2022_Accepted_ALL_in_one.csv: 45 ML Reproducibility Challenge 2022 accepted
  papers (title, authors, re_article, re_details).
Paper's claim: citation context sentiment correlates with reproducibility; citations
can signal reproducibility of the cited ML paper.
